                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">012.3/7904a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="to">Cole</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-20T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 20, 1942—midnight.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>343. For Murphy. Your 691.<note n="99" xml:id="d402fn99">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_398">p. 398</ref>.</note> You
                    are requested to forward the following message to Admiral Darlan from Admiral
                    Leahy: <pb facs="0407" n="401" xml:id="pg_401"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I hope you will accept my sympathy in your son’s illness, as well as our
                            hopes for his complete and early recovery.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
